LOS ANGELES, Dec. 15-- Walt Disney, who built his whimsical cartoon world of Mickey Mouse, Donald Duck and Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs into a $100-million-ayear entertainment empire, died in St. Joseph's Hospital here this morning. He was 65 years old. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
